  "key_detection_rules": {
    "description": "Heuristics for identifying likely key from a sequence of chords",
    "rules": [
      "Major chord appearing most frequently is likely I or IV or V",
      "If both a major chord and its relative minor appear, check which feels like home",
      "A dominant 7th chord strongly suggests V7 resolving to the key a fifth below",
      "The chord the progression resolves to (especially at phrase endings) is likely I",
      "vi-IV-I-V and I-V-vi-IV both suggest the major chord as I",
      "A minor chord followed by its relative major suggests the major key",
      "Three major chords a fifth apart (e.g., G-C-D) strongly suggest the middle one is I"
    ]
  }
